"{\"uid\": \"lgbtqnation.com-2024-08-restaurateur-who-boycotted-anti-christian-olympics-arrested-for-rape-kidnapping-murder\", \"text\": \"Bobby George made headlines after calling the Opening Ceremony \\\"insulting\\\" to Christians. Now he's accused of brutally assaulting a young woman.  An Ohio restaurant owner who attracted attention for banning Olympic broadcasts at his four Ohio eateries after calling them anti-Christian is now facing charges of rape, kidnapping and attempted murder.  Bobby George, 43,made headlinestwo weeks ago when he announced that his restaurant group was \\\"protesting\\\" the ParisOlympicsover what he described as a sacrilegious \\\"portrayal of 'The Last Supper'\\\" in the event's opening ceremony. The famous 1498 painting by gay artists Leonardo DaVinci depicted the final meal Jesus shared with his apostles before his crucifixion, according to Gospel accounts.  \\\"[The portrayal was] handled with an irresponsible level of irreverence, insulting the Christian faith,\\\" George posted inan announcement on Instagramand on signs at his restaurants. Right-wingers complained about the inclusion of drag queens in the portrayal, however, Olympic officials said it wasinspired by the Greek Festival of Dionysus, not \\\"The Last Supper.\\\"  More recently, police reports obtained byCleveland.comsaid that George assaulted his victim-a 25-year-old woman living with him over the past year-multiple times, threatened her with a gun and beat her so severely that she had to be treated by a nurse practitioner\\u00a0who worked with George's very own restaurant group.  \\\"You think God is going to help you?\\\" George allegedly taunted the woman as he shoved a towel down her throat and choked her, according to police. George also mocked her for praying to God, saying that she would not die during one of his multiple attacks, the reports added.  The abuse began in September 2023 and only ended last month, police said.  The restauranteur turned himself in on Friday after a warrant was issued for his arrest on charges of attempted murder, rape, felony assault, four counts of kidnapping and two counts of strangulation.  George was released on a $200,000 bond Tuesday after appearing in Cleveland Municipal Court. In a protection order, the judge barred George from contacting his alleged victim.  The woman \\\"fears for her life,\\\" according to court documents.  In the first attack detailed by police, George allegedly threw his victim into a kitchen cabinet so hard that the glass shattered.  The next month, George pinned her to the floor, choked her and slammed her head into a table repeatedly. Police say she suffered blurred vision and bleeding and ringing in her ears afterwards.  \\\"The defendant then had victim treated by his business'(s) nurse-practitioner who diagnosed her with post-concussion syndrome,\\\" according to a report by the Cleveland police Domestic Violence Unit contained in the arrest warrant.  George is accused of shoving a gun in the woman's stomach after she tried to flee his home, of raping her after she exited a shower, and of choking her on multiple occasions.  \\\"Defendant pulled her hair, strangled her and threw her all over the house,\\\" a Cleveland police detective wrote.  George's attorney, Kevin Spellacy, denied the allegations.  Greg Owenwrites about politics and culture for LGBTQ Nation. An award-winning writer, producer and journalist, he was recently recognized for Excellence in Online Journalism by NLGJA: the Association of LGBTQ Journalists for his coverage of the 2024 election. He's written for Q Digital since 2015 and for LGBTQ Nation since 2022.  Connect with Greg Owen:  See more:Crime & Justice,anti-Christian,Bobby George,Christianity,Festival of Dionysus,Ohio,Paris Olympics,The Last Supper  Over 400 trans flags were stolen from a Trans Day of Remembrance memorial. Police have no leads.  Wife of lesbian astronaut pleads guilty in \\\"far out\\\" space case involving fraud & theft  Two women injured as LGBTQ+ bars shot up in San Diego  Mainstream media leaves out our stories. We do not. LGBTQ Nation is LGBTQ+ owned, operated, and reader-supported. Join the members who keep our journalism free for millions of readers.  Or give a different amount:  We accept all major credit cards, Apple\\u00a0Pay, and\\u00a0Google\\u00a0Pay.  Quitter: Marjorie Taylor Greene announces that she's leaving the House in January  Wife of lesbian astronaut pleads guilty in \\\"far out\\\" space case involving fraud & theft  \\\"I will do anything to save him\\\": Watch 7 unshakable parents demand rights for their trans kids  A fan asked \\\"Real Housewives\\\" to show support for trans rights. It led to this heartwarming moment.  Anti-\\\"woke\\\" dad accused teachers of \\\"grooming\\\" kids. He got hit with a $20 million lawsuit.  The court declared that EU citizens have a right to \\\"a normal family life\\\" regardless of borders.  A Democratic super PAC alleged that she had been an escort on a \\\"sugar daddy\\\" website.  She co-edited the influential anthology \\\"Bi Any Other Name\\\" and helped bring bi activism into the modern era.  Craig is an adoptive parent herself who had to fight anti-gay discrimination in court to adopt her son.  The judge wrote he was \\\"not persuaded in the least\\\" by the DOJ's rationale for needing the information.  The group behind the memorial called it a hate crime \\\"that directly echoes the very violence and prejudice that TDOR was established to condemn.\\\"  \\\"No one came to help them,\\\" one person said about how people cheered while the women were attacked.  \\\"The Government has effectively sacrificed a generation of trans youth,\\\" said one civil rights organization.  You never know whose life you might be touching.  Erica Deuso's campaign is reflective of how trans and gay politicians are shaping political campaign strategies.  Coach Jackie J once thought being gay meant she could not have a family. Representation may have changed everything.  The author went public in a tweet with what she told the census.  The group behind the memorial called it a hate crime \\\"that directly echoes the very violence and prejudice that TDOR was established to condemn.\\\"  \\\"Loud plops. Pop, pop, pop,\\\" a witness said. \\\"I heard that and saw everyone scramble outside.\\\"  The actor's husband wrote about the murder in an emotional Facebook post shortly after.  \\\"I made some poor decisions,\\\" he later explained to the judge.  Girlalala was a beloved wig stylist on TikTok and Instagram. Now, fans are mourning her tragic death.  The high school is facing three federal lawsuits all centered around how football players allegedly got away with violently tormenting their classmates.  Now he's facing the music.  Their flag had extra stripes, setting it apart from the common six-striped rainbow flag seen at Prides across the country.  She and her partner were shamed when a guard marched them out of a crowded women's restroom.  Four people were killed and more than a dozen others injured.  He shared a meme on social media about how churches make women feel unsafe if they let LGBTQ+ people in.  Coming amid a blue wave in Virginia, the attack hits differently for the owners of Gardening Gays Farm.  \\u00a9 2010 - 2025\\u00a0LGBTQ Nation\\u00ae | Proudly\\u00a0LGBTQ+ Owned\\u00a0and\\u00a0Operated\\u00a0\\ud83c\\udff3\\ufe0f\\u200d\\ud83c\\udf08\\u00a0\\ud83c\\udff3\\ufe0f\\u200d\\u26a7\\ufe0f  LGBTQ Nation is a registered trademark of Q.Digital, Inc., registered in the state of California.\"}"